title: For Sale:  Barrett MRAD 27" 1/9 twist 338 Lapua Mag
postcontent:
Ready to follow your every move, the MRAD adapts to a variety of user needs without sacrificing performance. With unrelenting precision and unfailing accuracy, this bolt action newcomer has already defined a whole new class of long-range rifles.

The MRAD rifle’s user-changeable barrel system is just one example of this hardworking gun’s modularity. The precision-grade barrel can be removed by simply unscrewing two bolts using a standard Torx wrench. Besides reducing maintenance and logistical burdens, this unique design paves the way for future caliber interchangeability and serviceability.

The MRAD also boasts Barrett’s new easily accessed trigger module. This match-grade trigger is drop-fire-proof and combat-ready. The thumb-operated safety can be configured for left or right hand operation. The ambidextrous magazine release can be used intuitively while retaining a firing grip and cheek weld.

Integrated into the MRAD rifle’s 7000 series aluminum upper receiver is an M1913 rail with 30 MOA taper and 21.75 inches of rail space. The configurable side and bottom rails can also hold a number of accessories.

The MRAD rifle’s stock is foldable for enhanced portability yet locks in as solid as a fixed-stock rifle, creating a rigid platform for consistent firing. When folded, the stock latches around the bolt handle for added security during transport. Because the stock folds to the bolt handle side of the action, the rifle is the same width overall, folded or extended.

Made of a temperature-resistant polymer, the adjustable cheek piece also offers a consistent rifle-to-user contact point. The rifle’s length of pull can be set to five different positions with the push of a single button.

From its quick-detach sling mounts to the Barrett Multi-Role Brown color of the rifle that blends into any environment—every detail of the MRAD has been carefully designed to create one thing: a high-performance rifle you can truly make your own.

Features:
Bolt guide acts as a dust cover to reduce contaminants
Accepts standard M4/M16 pistol grips
Ambidextrous magazine release
Front-loading barrel design for caliber interchangeability
Single button for length of pull adjustment
Combat-proof trigger module removable without tools
Folding stock provides compact mobility

title: For Sale:  WTT-WTS-!!  RARE !! SIG-P220 chambered in 9mm
postcontent:
Rare caliber in the  P220

The SIG P220 has been made in 45acp for almost 40 years... from 1976-1979 there were four different calibers made in a model P220. 45acp,  38 super , 22 Long Rifle and 9mm.
The 38 Super being the most rare the 9mm caliber P220 was a production run for 3 years and have not been made since. Nor according to SigSauer will they ever be again.
There will not be any more of these 9mm P220's made.. additionally this Particular P220 has a stainless steel upper... which was only about 10% of the total production. The combination of the short run..and the rarity of the stainlesss steel slide make this particular gun fairly rare. If you are a serious SIG collector this would be a must-have. I would like for the gun to go home with someone who appreciates its rarity and the quality of the craftsmanship. The frame of the gun milled from aluminum has been cerakoated inside and out. It is hands down the best  coating I have seen done. The color is silver and makes areally nice contrast to the stainless steel slide. When Disassembled the gun is in pristine condition inside and out. and in fully functional  coniditon.. no visible wear on any internal or external parts. This is an excellent guin and would be a great additioon to any collection or  could be used as a daily carry.. great gun!
Original era correct wooden SIG handles.. currently these are only available for purchase frmo SIG online.. and they were  what was issued with the gun in 1976 when it was made. The slide and all functions are tight and crisp. Trigger pull is consistent through te pull.
The serial numebrs on the barrel frame and slide all match
 The magazine release is the european location on the bottom of the grip next to the mag as opposed to the american location. The gun is proof marked to have been made in germany

I am asking 800$ or best offer for the gun but would prefer a trade to a similar interesting gun.. preferrably in 45 or 40 caliber but may consider any firearm  trade

postcontent:
Model 70 Winchester, Coyote Light, chambered in 243 Winchester.

These rifles have a Bell & Carlson, aluminum pillar bedded Kevlar stock.  Black, with the baked on, easy grip finish.  It has the cooling holes in the forearm, & a black Decellerator pad.  It also has two swivel studs in the forearm (one for a bipod/accessory, & the other for a sling).

The receiver & the floor plate/trigger guard are matte blue, & the barrel is matte stainless, fluted, 24 inches long.  The action is Controlled Round Feed (CRF).  That would be a "claw" action, to you hard core model 70'ers.

It is in excellent condition.  Other then some discoloration, on the bolt, & a couple minor marks on the top of the barrel; there isn't a mark on it.  It has the smoothest action, I have ever seen, on any bolt action rifle.

We took a photo of the marks on the bolt.  We tried to photograph the marks on the top of the barrel, but they didn't show up in the photo.

We sold this rifle to a guy about two years ago, so we know it has been shot for about two years.  He came in & traded it for one of the new Coyotes, with the threaded barrel (the suppressor ready Coyote).

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 12 Riot Gun:  Attn. Cowboy Action Shooters.
postcontent:
This is a pre-64 Model 12 in 12 gauge, with the nickel steel barrel and 2.75" chamber. It began its career as a field grade 28" mod choke until I had the barrel professionally shortened and crowned and the bead reset for its current riot-gun configuration.

The gun is a 1954 issue, back from the peak of Winchester's quality, and is in excellent mechanical shape and very good cosmetic shape (only flaw is a small area of shallow pitting and bluing loss on left side of receiver). The solid, straight-grain black walnut stocks retain about 85% of their finish and are crack-free. The bluing and overall fit and finish are excellent. It has a cylinder-bored 20-inch barrel with a bead sight, and the chamber and bore are mirror-bright, as both have just been professionally honed and the barrel back-bored.

This would be an excellent Cowboy Action or Bowling Pin shotgun. It would also be a very good deer gun with slugs or buckshot in brush or tight cover. And, of course, it would make a very persuasive and effective home defense gun. As this model was one of the very few (with the Win. Model 97 and early Ithaca 37) ever built without a trigger disconnect, it can be slam-fired--almost as fast as an autoloader. It is short, well-balanced, and shucks lightning-fast. And, of course, it has that unmistakable heft and feel of a pre-64 Winchester, when polished blued steel and real walnut were standard equipment. Unlike today's cheap pumpguns, the only plastic part associated with this gun is the Winchester embossed buttplate. 

I have additional photos that I will gladly email upon request.

Serious inquiries only, please; do not reply if you are unable or unwilling to pass NICS. 

Respond to this post with a phone number and the best time to call. 

Will trade for: older side-by-side in 16 or 20 (i.e., Savage/Stevens/Fox B); Ithaca 37 deerslayer or featherlight; Winchester 94 levergun; centerfire bolt gun in a deer caliber; or .22 match/target rifle(s), bolt or rolling block.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Model 70 Winchester Coyote Light 243 Winchester SS Fluted Barrel 24"
postcontent:
Model 70 Winchester, Coyote Light, chambered in 243 Winchester.

These rifles have a Bell & Carlson, aluminum pillar bedded Kevlar stock.  Black, with the baked on, easy grip finish.  It has the cooling holes in the forearm, & a black Decellerator pad.  It also has two swivel studs in the forearm (one for a bipod/accessory, & the other for a sling).

The receiver & the floor plate/trigger guard are matte blue, & the barrel is matte stainless, fluted, 24 inches long.  The action is Controlled Round Feed (CRF).  That would be a "claw" action, to you hard core model 70'ers.

It is in excellent condition.  Other then some discoloration, on the bolt, & a couple minor marks on the top of the barrel; there isn't a mark on it.  It has the smoothest action, I have ever seen, on any bolt action rifle.

We took a photo of the marks on the bolt (we took the photo on 24x, so the discoloration would show up; consequently, it looks like the bolt is pitted; it isn’t, the finish on the bolt is silky smooth; these are just marks, & they are barely visible to the naked eye).  We tried to photograph the marks on the top of the barrel, but they didn't show up in the photo.

We sold this rifle to a guy about two years ago, so we know it has been shot for about two years.  He came in & traded it for one of the new Coyotes, with the threaded barrel (the suppressor ready Coyote).

From Vigilance Rifles:
408 Cheytac. The Holy Grail of rifle cartridges, especially when being shot by the VR1 rifles. Quick follow up shots and easy impact reading from the low recoil of the VR1 Rifles is one of the key advantages of stepping down to a 408 Cheytac cartridge from the much bigger 416 Barrett or 50 BMG rifles. Not to mention VR1 rifles only weigh 18 lb. which means you can actually take it some where. It is the cartridge that I designed the VR1 rifles to shoot, all other calibers that we offer just happen to fit in the VR1 Rifles.

Rocky Mountain Bullets has developed real 420 gn. RBBT bullets for the 408 Cheytac, it certainly has taken the 408 Cheytac to a new level in performance. With the new bullets shooters are able to achieve long periods of sustained fire before accuracy deteriorates due to fouling, compared to shooting solid monolithics. 

Distinctive from all others the VR1 is the only Semi-Auto Autoloader on the market chambered in the 408 Cheytac or 505 Gibbs. It is also available in 338 Lapua. The 408 Cheytac cartridge is a highbred, with confirmed kills out to 1 mile from trained hands. The VR1 holds five cartridges in 408 Cheytac - 505 Gibbs and 338 Lapua. The 338 Lapua is NATO and ammo is in military armaments, RAUFUS-AP-API are available, the cartridge proves well out to 1500 yards. VR1 shoots 1 MOA accuracy with 338 Lapua or 408 Cheytac in trained hands. The VR1 is not your typical M16 type conversion sniper rifle. We take great pride in the fact we completely manufacture it from the ground up. Our true 2-stage trigger with oil-lite bearings for a consistent reliable trigger pull. There are four sizes of bi pods and a mono pod available for different shooting requirements they change out in seconds. Our sling is attached to the internal frame of the rifle so an accidental dropping of the rifle due to sling pull is eliminated. The sling design also enables it to double as a turnacate. The Mill-Spec scope rail is mounted with (TORX-FHCS) this precision aligns the scope with the barrel eliminating bullet shift at different distances. Our safety is ambidextrous push type ( Fail Proof) with easy visual identification. We use a rotary screw bolt system that screws the bolt shut; this feature virtually eliminates the required force for opening and shutting the bolt. This is one of the key reasons that we are the only manufacturer able to make the 408 Cheytac cartridges shoot flawlessly in a Semi-Auto Autoloader. Rotary lock rifles usually use a spring loaded ejector, which can cause jams with high rate fire, the VR1 uses a Rotary screw bolt and fixed ejector for sure ejection and no jams. It is unusual to find a large caliber Semi-Auto Autoloader rifle that shoots as accurately and reliably as the VR1. 

BENEFITS - A Long-range PRECISION SNIPER RIFLE (PSR) with quick follow up shots due to low recoil of Semi-Auto operation and Auto loading. Quick detachable magazines for instant load selection and increased firepower. Robust sturdy design that easily assembles and breaks down with no tools in under a minute with no loss of bullet impact. Easily concealable, no assembly being longer than 33 inches. Variable caliber interchangeable barrels. A gas forward design allowing for longer periods before cleaning due to gases not entering the receiver area. Our list is long and all the innovations in this new rifle certainly cannot be described on a concise white paper. The technology and engineering in this rifle are instantly noticeable. 

Features:
Designed and developed to be light and mobile and inspired by several of the finest autoloading rifles in the world, we have taken the best features and incorporated them into a larger than life autoloading rifle.

Chambered in four exciting large calibers, the 338 Lapua, 375 Cheytac, 408 Cheytac and 505 Gibbs. The 338 Lapua for NATO, 375 and 408 Cheytac for long range engagement and the legendary 505 Gibbs made famous by Earnest Hemingway for unbeatable knockdown Power.

With five shots in the quick detachable magazine you’re sure to have plenty of firepower for the largest or most dangerous game. 

Reliability of the VR1 is due to the gas port being optimally located to the chamber. The gases are cleaner and hotter up front and result in more reliable cycling and less fowling, the best autoloading rifles in the world use this system.

Our upper receiver is made from 17-4 PH Stainless Steel and certified Heat Treatment for high-pressure operation with such large calibers. The upper receiver-barrel locks securely into a lightweight hard-anodized lower receiver. The rifle uses a three-lugged rotary screw bolt for sure lockup, and a fixed ejector for high rate fire.

Using a 11/4 Bull Barrel for extreme accuracy and incorporating a proven Titanium Muzzle Brake for taming the Beast, makes the VR1 easy to shoot in any of our four calibers. The VR1 Rifles come standard with our exclusive M1A style Glass Filled Nylon Stocks for all weather conditions and come standard with Coyote M1A CHEEKPAD. Optionally High Comb Stocks machined from (RUTPLY) premium wood are available in several colors.

Our exclusive Pendulum Two Stage Trigger (PTST) at the heart of the gun supplies crisp reliable trigger pull. First stage is 2-½ lb and second stage releases at 3-½ lb respectively, the predictability of the trigger improves shooter accuracy and confidence. Incorporated within the trigger system is a heavy engagement (FAIL PROOF) traditional push safety.
